{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
A '''dry punch''' is [[meteorology|meteorological]] slang for a [[Synoptic scale meteorology|synoptic scale]] or [[Mesoscale meteorology|mesoscale]] process. A dry punch at the surface results in a [[dry line]] bulge. A dry punch aloft above an area of warm, moist (buoyant) air at low levels often increases the potential for severe [[thunderstorm]]s.

== See also ==
* [[Dew point depression]]

