{{Infobox book | <!-- See [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Novels]] or [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Books]] --> | name = Engines | title_orig = | translator = | image = Engines de camp.jpg | image_size = 200px | caption = Cover of ''Engines'' | author = [[L. Sprague de Camp]] | illustrator = [[Jack Coggins]] | cover_artist = Lowell Hess | country = United States | language = English | series = | subject = [[Engineering]] | publisher = [[Golden Press]] | release_date = 1959 | english_release_date = | media_type = Print ([[Hardcover|Hardback]]) | pages = 56 pp | preceded_by = | followed_by = }} {{Portal |Children's literature}}
'''''Engines: Man's Use of Power, from the Water Wheel to the Atomic Pile''''' is a [[science book]] for children by [[L. Sprague de Camp]], illustrated by [[Jack Coggins]], published by [[Golden Press]] in 1959.<ref name="Laughlin">{{cite book | last=Laughlin | first=Charlotte |author2=Daniel J. H. Levack | title=De Camp: An L. Sprague de Camp Bibliography | location=San Francisco | publisher=Underwood/Miller | pages=52–53 | year=1983}}</ref><ref name="ISFDB">{{isfdb title|id=854647}}</ref><ref name="SNL">"Books of the Week" in ''The Science News-Letter'', v. 76, no. 3, July 18, 1959, page 44.</ref> A revised edition issued as part of the publisher's [[The Golden Library of Knowledge Series|Golden Library of Knowledge Series]] was published in 1961,<ref name="Laughlin"/> and a paperback edition in 1969.<ref name="ISFDB"/>
==Summary== As stated on the cover, the work is a survey of "Man's use of power, from the water wheel to the atomic pile."
==Reception== ''The Science News-Letter'', in its July 18, 1959 issue, listed the book among its "Books of the Week," describing the work as a "[f]actual book for young readers."<ref name="SNL"/>
