{{Infobox organization |name = International Energy Centre |bgcolor = |fgcolor = |image = |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = |motto = |formation = 2011 |extinction = |type = Not For Profit |status = |purpose = |headquarters = |location = Brisbane |region_served = Global |membership = |language = |leader_title = CEO |leader_name = [[Tim McLennan]] |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://www.internationalenergycentre.com] |remarks = }}
{{refimprove|date=January 2013}} The '''International Energy Centre''' (IEC) is a collaborative initiative established by three of Australia's leading universities ([[University of Western Australia]], [[University of Newcastle, Australia|University of Newcastle]] and [[University of Queensland]]), and foundation industry member Glencore Xstrata. IEC's vision is to create an established centre of excellence in thought leadership, postgraduate education and innovation management to support the transition to a sustainable low carbon world.
The Centre formed in 2011 with foundation sponsorship funding from [[Xstrata Coal]], a subsidiary of [[Xstrata]],<ref name="XC">[http://sustainability.xstratacoal.com/Documents/SD_Report_2011_LR_CASE-STUDY.pdf Xstrata Sustainability Report], Xstrata Coal joined forces with three Australian universities.</ref>(now Glencore Xstrata). The business model is based on the experience of the formation of the [[International Water Centre]], a joint venture between [[University of Western Australia]], [[University of Queensland]] (two of the three universities in the IEC) plus [[Griffith University]] and [[Monash University]]. Recently Glencore awarded scholarships to six Master of Energy Studies students.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.eco-business.com/press-releases/glencorexstrata-awards-six-scholarships-to-msc-energy-studies-students/ | title=GlencoreXstrata awards six scholarships to MSc Energy Studies students | work=Press Release | date=4 March 2014 | agency=Eco-Business | accessdate=9 March 2014}}</ref>
