{{expand Russian|topic=bio|Милов, Владимир Станиславович|date=March 2014}} [[File:2017 Halifax International Security Forum (38473649942).jpg|thumb|Milov at the [[Halifax International Security Forum]] 2017]] '''Vladimir Stanislavovich Milov''' ({{lang-ru|link=no|Влади́мир Станисла́вович Мило́в}}, born 18 June 1972 in [[Kemerovo]]) is a Russian politician and the former president of the [[Institute of Energy Policy]], a Moscow-based independent [[think tank]].<ref>http://www.rusprofile.ru/id/2838796</ref> He is the former Deputy Energy Minister of the Russian Federation.<ref>[http://www.novostroy.ru/law/direct.php?num=1488203&id=91&sort=num2&type=gov Сообщение для печати № 762. Распоряжение от 14 мая 2002 г. № 613-р О заместителе Министра энергетики Российской Федерации]</ref>
==Biography== Vladimir Milov graduated from [[Moscow State Mining University]] in 1994. In 1997–2001, he worked for the [[natural monopoly]] regulator of Russia, the Federal Energy Commission of Russia, serving in 1999–2001 as the head of its economic analysis department. In 2001 he headed an expert team within the [[Center for Strategic Research (Russia)|Center for Strategic Research]], a government-linked think tank.<ref name=russiahouse>{{Cite web|title=Vladimir Milov (Russia) |publisher=Russia House |url=http://www.russiahouse.org/wrf/Vladimir_Milov.htm |accessdate=2009-10-18 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090625185649/http://www.russiahouse.org/wrf/Vladimir_Milov.htm |archivedate=June 25, 2009 }} </ref><ref name=salzburg> {{Cite web | title = Vladimir Milov | publisher = Salzburg Global Seminar | url= http://www.salzburgglobal.org/2009/includes/FacultyPopUp.cfm?IDSPECIAL_EVENT=830&IDRecords=115950 | accessdate = 2009-10-18}} </ref><ref name=carnegie> {{Cite web | title = Vladimir Milov | publisher = [[Carnegie Endowment]] | url= http://www.carnegieendowment.org/experts/index.cfm?fa=expert_view&expert_id=350&prog=zru | accessdate = 2009-10-18}} </ref>
In December 2001, Milov was appointed adviser to the Minister of Energy of the Russian Federation and in May 2002, he was appointed Deputy Minister of Energy of Russia in [[Mikhail Kasyanov|Kasyanov's]] government. He resigned in October 2002.<ref name=russiahouse/><ref name=salzburg/>
In December 2008, Milov co-founded the opposition movement "[[Solidarnost]]". He was one of the leaders of the organization until May 2010. In February 2010, Milov was elected a leader of the social movement "Democratic Choice". He resigned on December 20, 2015 after a series of internal disagreements. Since 2016, Milov has been actively participating in [[Alexei Navalny presidential campaign, 2018|Alexei Navalny's presidential campaign]]. Milov was mentioned as one of the co-authors of Navalny's platform that was published on December 13, 2017.<ref>[https://2018.navalny.com/platform Программа Алексея Навального]</ref>
